---
import Layout from "../Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Slack app">
  <div
    class="py-16 2xl:py-32 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-16 md:gap-4 lg:gap-8"
  >
    <figure>
      <img
        src="https://gif.land/owlbow.jpg"
        width={500}
        height={375}
        alt="An little owl in a bowtie"
      />
      <figcaption class="text-sm flex flex-col">
        <a
          class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-emerald-700 dark:hover:text-emerald-500"
          target="_blank"
          href="https://gif.land/owlbow.jpg"
        >
          owlbow.jpg
        </a>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
    <div
      class="-mt-px max-w-lg [&_p]:my-4 [&_p]:text-pretty [&_a]:underline [&_a]:underline-offset-2 [&_a]:hover:text-emerald-700 [&_a]:dark:hover:text-emerald-500"
    >
      <h3 class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-none">
        you asked, we delivered
      </h3>
      <h2 class="text-2xl">gif.land in your Slack</h2>
      <p>Because sometimes copy/pasting a url is hard.</p>
      <p>
        Get the gifs super fast: type
        <code
          class="font-mono text-sm bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-700 px-2 py-1 text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-300"
          >/gifland</code
        > for a random gif<br /> or <code
          class="font-mono text-sm bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-700 px-2 py-1 text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-300"
          >/gifland [keyword]</code
        > to search the whole catalogue.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="https://slack.gif.land/slack/install"
          ><img
            alt="Add to Slack"
            height="40"
            width="139"
            src="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png"
            srcSet="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png 1x, https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack@2x.png 2x"
          /></a
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        The app is a cloudflare worker, <a
          href="https://github.com/jonheslop/gif-land-slack"
          >hereâ€™s the source code</a
        >, it uses <a href="/api">this endpoint</a> which is all the gifs in json.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
